{
  "texts": [
    "They formulated a multi-objective problem to balance the estimation performance, communication rate, and power consumption, which was solved via multi-task learning with low overhead.",
    "Saikia et al. [232] investigated the resource allocation within the IRS-aided cooperative ISAC network, where multiple BSs detected the targets in sequence and served the users cooperatively.",
    "The squared position error bound was minimized via joint transmit beamforming, phase shift, and subcarrier allocation design.",
    "To deal with this high-dimension mixed integer optimization problem, they proposed a hybrid DRL algorithm, which can handle both continuous and discrete actions.",
    "Hossain et al. [233] investigated the E2E network slicing for ISAC systems and the E2E latency was minimized by optimizing the transmission and resource for both communication and sensing."
  ]
}